Players play with the top card of their libraries revealed.
You may play the top card of any player's library.
Whenever you roll CHAOS, each player puts the top card of his or her library into his or her graveyard.

name: Windrider Eel
text:
Flying
Landfall — Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, Windrider Eel gets +2/+2 until end of turn.

editions.flavor:
"The best spot to hook one is right behind the gills."
—Rana Cloudwake, kor skyfisher

name: Windrider Patrol
text:
Flying
Whenever Windrider Patrol deals combat damage to a player, scry 2. (Look at the top two cards of your library, then put any number of them on the bottom of your library and the rest on top in any order.)

name: Wind Sail
text: One or two target creatures gain flying until end of turn.

editions.flavor: It pays to be at home both on the sea and in the sky.
It pays to be at home both on the sea and in the sky.

name: Wind-Scarred Crag
text:
Wind-Scarred Crag enters the battlefield tapped.
When Wind-Scarred Crag enters the battlefield, you gain 1 life.
{T}: Add {R} or {W} to your mana pool.

name: Windscouter
text:
Flying
When Windscouter attacks or blocks, return it to its owner's hand at end of combat. (Return it only if it's on the battlefield.)

editions.flavor: These nimble ships were designed for hit-and-run tactics.

name: Windseeker Centaur
text: Vigilance

editions.flavor: Loyal and passionate in battle, the Windseeker tribe roams the Green Lands near the Honeyed Sea.

name: Wind Shear
text: Attacking creatures with flying get -2/-2 and lose flying until end of turn.

editions.flavor:
"As the winds abated, there was a shower of dragonscales, then nothing more."
—Azeworai, "The Unruly Wind"

name: Winds of Change
text: Each player shuffles the cards from his or her hand into his or her library, then draws that many cards.

editions.flavor: "‘Tis the set of sails, and not the gales,/ Which tells us the way to go." —Ella Wheeler Wilcox
